<info>
<title>Preface</title>
</info>

<para>In this example, the media are stored in the same hierarchy as
the XML sources. The sources are all in the same directory. Some of
the media are in a subdirectory, but the references are all
relative to the document(s).</para>

<mediaobject>
<imageobject>
<imagedata fileref="duck-left.png"/>
</imageobject>
</mediaobject>

<mediaobject>
<imageobject>
<imagedata fileref="duck-right.png"/>
</imageobject>
</mediaobject>

<mediaobject>
  <videoobject>
    <videodata fileref="media/spinning-top.mp4" width="360"/>
  </videoobject>
</mediaobject>

<mediaobject>
  <audioobject>
    <audiodata fileref="media/this_is_a_test.mp3">
      <multimediaparam name="controls" value="controls"/>
    </audiodata>
  </audioobject>
</mediaobject>

<para>What follows is a reference to an external video identified with
an absolute uri.</para>

<mediaobject>
  <videoobject>
    <?db video="iframe"?>
    <videodata width="560" depth="315" scalefit="1"
               fileref="https://www.youtube.com/embed/twj8G5_hu_0">
      <multimediaparam name="frameborder" value="0"/>
      <multimediaparam name="allow"
                       value="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"/>
      <multimediaparam name="allowfullscreen" value="allowfullscreen"/>
      <multimediaparam name="controls" value="controls"/>
    </videodata>
  </videoobject>
</mediaobject>

<para>Absolute URIs arenâ€™t changed by mediaobject processing.</para>

</preface>
